main event: A civilian observed a reddish-bluish colored object disappear into the clouds in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania on July 12, 1966.
interesting points: The object was shaped like a banana.
The initial reported information conflicted with the completed form, including different times and length of observation.
There was no sound at all heard from the object.
The object appeared to travel and then remained stationary, but did not move at all.
The observer estimated the object was about 1000 feet away and compared its size to covering about half of a match head held at arm's length.
sighted object: A reddish-bluish colored object shaped like a banana
